Linux System Monitoring Commands:
  top     -> Process & Resource Usage
  vmstat  -> System Performance related to CPU, RAM, Processes, IO
  free    -> Information about Memory
  iostat  -> IO Statistics
  netstat -> Network Statistics
  iotop   -> Monitor disk io usage
  htop    -> Enhanced - Interactive version of the top command
  atop    -> Advanced System Monitoring
  nmon    -> Analyze CPU, memory, disk, network and process performance
  iftop   -> Network Bandwidth Usage
